Package ristretto.problem.fs.subset.breed

Class FSSubsetCrossoverPipeline

  • java.lang.Object
    • ec.BreedingSource
      • ec.BreedingPipeline
        • ristretto.problem.fs.subset.breed.FSSubsetCrossoverPipeline
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ec.Prototype, ec.Setup, ec.steadystate.SteadyStateBSourceForm, ec.util.RandomChoiceChooserD, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable
    public class FSSubsetCrossoverPipeline
extends ec.BreedingPipeline
    FSSubsetCrossoverPipeline is a BreedingPipeline which implements a simple default crossover for a FSSubsetIndividual. Normally it takes two individuals and returns two crossed-over child individuals. Optionally, it can take two individuals, cross them over, but throw away the second child (a one-child crossover). FSSubsetCrossoverPipeline works by calling FSSubsetIndividual.defaultCrossover(ec.EvolutionState, int, ristretto.problem.fs.subset.FSSubsetIndividual) on the first parent individual. It has been adapted from the original ECJ's VectorCrossoverPipeline.java (Copyright 2006 by Sean Luke under the AFL v. 3.0) to grab and produce FSSubsetIndividuals.

    Typical Number of Individuals Produced Per produce(...) call
    2 * minimum typical number of individuals produced by each source, unless tossSecondParent is set, in which case it's simply the minimum typical number.

    Number of Sources
    2

    Parameters

    base.toss
    bool = true or false (default)    		 (after crossing over with the first new individual, should its second sibling individual be thrown away instead of adding it to the population?)

    Default Base
    fs-subset.xover
